body.description: Blast off for adventure in this fun and graphic Outer Space complete bedroom ensemble! The comforter face features an allover design of photorealistic planets and space probes on a star-strewn midnight blue ground, accented by a wide decorative band featuring planets, satellites and the space shuttle; the comforter reverse, flanged pillow shams and bed skirt all feature the allover star design. The 180-thread-count percale sheets and pillowcases feature smaller-scale images of planets and space probes on a crisp white ground, accented with a narrow band of the star design. All components are constructed of a cotton-rich blend of 60% cotton and 40% polyester, and are machine washable.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Every Night Starts with A Dream There’s something special about bedtime. The stories we tell, the softness of a warm bed, and the little stuffed friends that we can’t live without. At Dream Factory, we’re inspired by the magic of bedtime. We tell our stories through cozy bedding, playful bathroom accessories and whimsical window curtains. Have a good night every night and come dream with us.

Dreams Come True Designed by moms Approved by kids. As mothers, we want the best for our young dreamers. Each design is carefully crafted to be soft, comfortable, durable, and easy to care for. This goes hand in hand for each whimsical pattern we design. We listen to the playful stories our kids tell. We echo their colorful imagination in our bedding, bath accessories, and window curtains. The Quality of your dreams Carefully crafted designs call for consciously sourced production. At Dream Factory, quality production is our priority. We select from the best factories to produce our styles safely and with proper care. We use fabrics that feel good on your children’s skin so they are comfortable all night long. We make your life (and ours) a little bit easier with durable fabrics that maintain its softness and vibrant colors wash after wash. Easy to care for We know from experience that your little one’s bedding has to be durable. They sleep all night in it and jump on it during the day. At Dream Factory, we designed each bed to withstand wear and tear with durable fabrics. Our styles are machine washable so they can be cared for easily. The colors will stay vibrant and touch will always be soft. Each style can be played in, lived in and dreamed in. What's included? Bring your little one’s imagination to life with Dream Factory. Making the bed of their dreams is simple with our curated bed in a bag. Our Bed in a bag includes a comforter, flat sheet, fitted sheet, pillowcase, sham and bed skirt. It’s the perfect way to enliven their room with fun patterns that they will love and comfort that you can trust.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2011
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This ain't pottery barn, people...
reviews.reviewText: I was reluctant to order from this seller because of some of the reviews. However, my experience was very good. The full size set arrived quickly. It appears to be well made, and looks, well, just like the picture. For the price it's a good value. Yes, the comforter fabric is a little stiff and not super thick, but it washed well and that seemed to help with the softness some. This set is not "oversized" at all, but I would say it it true to size. The mattress I put it on is a little thicker than standard, so it doesn't cover it the way I would like, but it's fine. And, it's for a 6 years old kids room...the most important thing is, he loves it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 9, 2011
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Surprised by the quality!
reviews.reviewText: I ordered this when a local big box store was sold out of the outer space themed bedding I had so badly wanted for my son's room. I didn't have high hopes for the quality as it is a bed in a bag and my experience has always been the sheets are of lesser quality than those purchased individually. Boy was I wrong! The comforter, shams, and sheets were all very well made, there is a nice weight to the comforter and the sheets don't have that polyester feel to them. They are 50/50 blend and very pretty! I was pleasantly surprised to say the least and the price was right!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 26, 2014
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This is cool and comfy!
reviews.reviewText: It was really hard to find space themed bedding - so glad we found this. It's not the softest comforter in the world but might be softer after a few more washings. It is a great weight though - not too hot and not too cold. It looks great in my son's space themed room. Wish there were matching curtains!Update: about 9 months after purchase, daily use and lots of washings this bedspread has held its color and shape. I'd say it's really well made!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 11, 2011
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful little comforter set
reviews.reviewText: This set was purchased for my granddaughter who wanted an astronomy theme in her bedroom. The colors are vivid and the fabric is a good quality although low thread count. The comforter was a good weight and appears to be of good quality. For an inexpensive set, it exceeded my expectations and made for a beautifully decorated room. Unlike one of the previous comments, the full-sized sheet set was true to size and fit very well. The shipping was fast and packaging was good. Very happy with the quality and shipping service.
